        "created_at": "2025-01-04T04:39:01.081Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A folder is a group of chats. A group is a group of people in one chat. I had a mishap the other day when I wanted to try out the new folder feature, where I added a bunch of people to a group chat, which immediately appeared for all these contacts before I had even sent a message in it. It was on Android.</p>\n<p>I wanted to bring up a discussion here about whether this stuff could be more fool-proofed, since leaking someones social graph can be consequential for many users. Solving/changing any of the following would have prevented the issue:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Call groups ‘group chats’ instead to make clear that ‘add group’ does not create a category of contacts, but a chat with all of the people in it.</li>\n<li>Don’t show the group chat for the people in it until the creator sends the first message.</li>\n<li>Don’t show the participant list of the group chat for people who are kicked out of the group.</li>\n<li>Once a contact deletes a group chat, don’t show members from that group chat when they are searching for contacts under ‘start new conversation’ unless they are already in their contact list.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I think 2 is reasonable from anyone’s perspective. The others I can see there being disagreement about.</p>",
